                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div x-data="{ open: false }" class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded-lg shadow">
                        <div class="accordion-header flex justify-between items-center" @click="open = !open">
                            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-600">Step 4 – Take your documents to have them legally certified</h2>
                            <span x-text="open ? '−' : '+'" class="text-2xl text-blue-600"></span>
                        </div>
                        <div x-show="open" x-cloak class="accordion-content mt-3 text-neutral-700 space-y-2">
                            <p class="font-semibold">Only for applicants who do not currently hold an NQF approved qualification.</p>
                            <p>ACECQA requires certain documents to be provided as certified colour copies of your originals. Take both your original document and a colour copy to a legally authorised person. Certifications must be in English, and applicants must not certify their documents themselves.</p>
                            <p>Refer to the <a href="https://www.acecqa.gov.au/media/28646" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">certifying documents information sheet</a>.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div x-data="{ open: false }" class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded-lg shadow">
                        <div class="accordion-header flex justify-between items-center" @click="open = !open">
                            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-600">Step 5 – Prepare your employment evidence</h2>
                            <span x-text="open ? '−' : '+'" class="text-2xl text-blue-600"></span>
                        </div>
                        <div x-show="open" x-cloak class="accordion-content mt-3 text-neutral-700 space-y-2">
                            <p>ACECQA requires evidence of how you demonstrated your skills while employed in the nominated occupation. You must provide two employment templates:</p>
                            <ol class="list-decimal list-inside ml-4">
                                <li>Have your employers/referees complete the <a href="https://www.acecqa.gov.au/media/41036" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Employer Reference Template</a>.</li>
                                <li>Complete your <a href="https://www.acecqa.gov.au/media/41031" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Employment Experience Template</a>.</li>
                            </ol>
                            <p>These must be completed by you and your direct supervisor and address the assessment standards for your occupation. Templates prepared by someone else will not be accepted.</p>
                             <div class="mt-8 bg-blue-100 p-6 rounded-lg shadow">
                                <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-700 mb-4 text-center">✨ Employment Evidence Assistant</h3>
                                <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-700">Enter your job duties/experience, and get suggestions on how to phrase them for your DAMA assessment.</p>
                                <div class="space-y-4">
                                    <div>
                                        <label for="employmentDuties" class="block text-sm font-medium text-neutral-700 mb-1">Describe your key job duties and responsibilities:</label>
                                        <textarea id="employmentDuties" rows="4" class="w-full p-2 border border-neutral-300 rounded-md focus:ring-blue-500 focus:border-blue-500"></textarea>
                                    </div>
                                    <div>
                                        <label for="employmentOccupation" class="block text-sm font-medium text-neutral-700 mb-1">Your Nominated Occupation:</label>
                                        <select id="employmentOccupation" class="w-full p-2 border border-neutral-300 rounded-md focus:ring-blue-500 focus:border-blue-500">
                                            <option value="">Select Occupation</option>
                                            <option value="Child Care Worker">Child Care Worker</option>
                                            <option value="Family Day Care Worker">Family Day Care Worker</option>
                                            <option value="Out of School Hours Care Worker">Out of School Hours Care Worker</option>
                                            <option value="Preschool Aide">Preschool Aide</option>
                                        </select>
                                    </div>
                                    <button id="suggestEmploymentPhrasesBtn" class="w-full bg-blue-600 text-white py-2 px-4 rounded-md hover:bg-blue-700 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:ring-offset-2 transition duration-300">
                                        Get Phrasing Suggestions
                                    </button>
                                    <div id="employmentPhrasesLoading" class="text-center text-blue-600 mt-2 hidden">Generating suggestions...</div>
                                    <div id="employmentPhrasesOutput" class="mt-4 p-4 bg-white border border-neutral-300 rounded-md llm-output hidden"></div>
                                    <p class="text-xs text-neutral-500 mt-2">Disclaimer: These suggestions are AI-generated for guidance only. Always ensure accuracy and truthfulness in your official documents.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div x-data="{ open: false }" class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded-lg shadow">
                        <div class="accordion-header flex justify-between items-center" @click="open = !open">
                            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-600">Step 6 – Scan your documents for uploading</h2>
                            <span x-text="open ? '−' : '+'" class="text-2xl text-blue-600"></span>
                        </div>
                        <div x-show="open" x-cloak class="accordion-content mt-3 text-neutral-700 space-y-2">
                            <p>To provide an ‘Assessment Ready’ application, documents must be:</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4">
                                <li>Colour copy in high resolution (photographs preferred).</li>
                                <li>Clearly visible (no blurry/illegible documents).</li>
                                <li>In colour and correctly certified (if applicable, see Step 4).</li>
                                <li>Centred on the page, showing all edges.</li>
                                <li>In an acceptable file format (.PDF, .JPEG, .PNG).</li>
                                <li>Titled appropriately.</li>
                                <li>Collated in correct page order (multi-page documents in one file).</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p class="text-red-700 font-semibold">Do not use GoogleDrive or other unsecured cloud links.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div x-data="{ open: false }" class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded-lg shadow">
                        <div class="accordion-header flex justify-between items-center" @click="open = !open">
                             <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-600">Step 7 – Begin online application and make payment</h2>
                            <span x-text="open ? '−' : '+'" class="text-2xl text-blue-600"></span>
                        </div>
                        <div x-show="open" x-cloak class="accordion-content mt-3 text-neutral-700 space-y-2">
                            <p>The online application takes about 40 minutes. Upload high-resolution, appropriately titled documents via the provided links.</p>
                            <p>The 60-day assessment period starts only after an ‘Assessment Ready’ application is provided. It is your (and your agent's) responsibility to ensure this.</p>
                            <p class="font-semibold">Submitting on behalf of someone else?</p>
                            <p>Both applicants and agents need to register with a genuine personal email address for portal access. Generic emails (e.g., info@email.com) are not accepted.</p>
                            <p>Pay the <a href="https://www.acecqa.gov.au/resources/applications/indexation-of-fees#part2" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">application fee</a> at the end. No submission without payment. No refunds for unsuccessful or withdrawn applications post-submission.</p>
                            <p>FAQ: <a href="https://www.acecqa.gov.au/help/faq" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">DAMA skills assessments FAQ</a>.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div x-data="{ open: false }" class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded-lg shadow">
                        <div class="accordion-header flex justify-between items-center" @click="open = !open">
                            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-600">Step 8 – What happens to my application?</h2>
                            <span x-text="open ? '−' : '+'" class="text-2xl text-blue-600"></span>
                        </div>
                        <div x-show="open" x-cloak class="accordion-content mt-3 text-neutral-700 space-y-2">
                            <p>ACECQA will email you within 10 working days of receiving your application.</p>
                            <p>Assessment is typically completed within 60 days of receiving all required information. Delays occur if information/documents are missing.</p>
                            <p class="text-red-700 font-semibold">Giving false or misleading information is a serious offence. ACECQA verifies information and will notify relevant authorities if discrepancies are found.</p>
                            <p>Personal information is stored according to the Australian Privacy Principles and ACECQA's <a href="https://www.acecqa.gov.au/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">privacy policy</a>.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div x-data="{ open: false }" class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded-lg shadow">
                        <div class="accordion-header flex justify-between items-center" @click="open = !open">
                            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-600">Step 9/10 - How do I receive my outcome?</h2>
                            <span x-text="open ? '−' : '+'" class="text-2xl text-blue-600"></span>
                        </div>
                        <div x-show="open" x-cloak class="accordion-content mt-3 text-neutral-700 space-y-2">
                            <p>ACECQA will notify you of the outcome by email.</p>
                            <p>If successful, you can submit your DAMA skills assessment for your visa application. A successful assessment does not guarantee visa grant.</p>
                            <p>If unsuccessful, you will receive reasons. You can request a review if you have additional evidence or believe provided evidence was not adequately considered:</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4">
                                <li>Child Care Worker: <a href="https://www.acecqa.gov.au/qualifications/provisional-skills-assessment/request-review-your-skills-assessment" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Request a review</a></li>
                                <li>Family Day Care Worker / Out of School Hours Care Worker: <a href="https://www.acecqa.gov.au/request-review-your-skills-assessment-new-page" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Request a review</a></li>
                            </ul>
                            <div class="mt-8 bg-blue-100 p-6 rounded-lg shadow">
                                <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-700 mb-4 text-center">✨ Review Request Draft Assistant</h3>
                                <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-700">Draft a concise and effective request for review if your application was unsuccessful.</p>
                                <div class="space-y-4">
                                    <div>
                                        <label for="reviewReason" class="block text-sm font-medium text-neutral-700 mb-1">Reason for requesting a review (e.g., "Additional evidence available", "Evidence not adequately considered"):</label>
                                        <textarea id="reviewReason" rows="3" class="w-full p-2 border border-neutral-300 rounded-md focus:ring-blue-500 focus:border-blue-500"></textarea>
                                    </div>
                                    <div>
                                        <label for="reviewOutcome" class="block text-sm font-medium text-neutral-700 mb-1">Summary of the unsuccessful outcome (e.g., "Qualification not recognized", "Insufficient work experience"):</label>
                                        <textarea id="reviewOutcome" rows="3" class="w-full p-2 border border-neutral-300 rounded-md focus:ring-blue-500 focus:border-blue-500"></textarea>
                                    </div>
                                    <button id="draftReviewRequestBtn" class="w-full bg-blue-600 text-white py-2 px-4 rounded-md hover:bg-blue-700 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:ring-offset-2 transition duration-300">
                                        Draft Review Request
                                    </button>
                                    <div id="reviewRequestLoading" class="text-center text-blue-600 mt-2 hidden">Drafting request...</div>
                                    <div id="reviewRequestOutput" class="mt-4 p-4 bg-white border border-neutral-300 rounded-md llm-output hidden"></div>
                                    <p class="text-xs text-neutral-500 mt-2">Disclaimer: This draft is AI-generated for guidance. Always review and customize it, and seek professional advice for official submissions.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <section id="support" class="pt-16 -mt-16 mb-12">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-sky-700 mb-8 text-center">Rural Realities & Support Systems</h2>
            <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
                <p class="mb-6 text-lg leading-relaxed">
                    Relocating to and working in rural Queensland presents a unique blend of challenges and rewarding opportunities. Understanding these specific realities, coupled with awareness of available support systems and government initiatives, is key for both international migrants and sponsoring employers to ensure a successful, sustainable, and mutually beneficial placement. This section delves deeper into these aspects.
                </p>
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div class="bg-amber-50 p-4 rounded-lg shadow">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-sky-600 mb-3">Relocation & Integration Challenges for Migrants</h3>
                        <p class="mb-2">Moving to a new country, especially a rural area, comes with its own set of hurdles:</p>
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 text-neutral-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Housing:</strong> Finding affordable and suitable accommodation can be challenging in rural areas, often requiring assistance with references, bond payments, and understanding local rental markets. Interim housing solutions upon arrival are often necessary.</li>
                            <li><strong>Cultural & Social Integration:</strong> Adapting to a new culture, local customs, and Australian English can be difficult. Access to social networks and community activities is vital to combat isolation. Migrants may also face subtle or overt discrimination.</li>
                            <li><strong>Access to Services:</strong> Navigating new healthcare systems, banking, transportation, and other essential services can be complex without proper guidance.</li>
                            <li><strong>Support Needs:</strong> Access to dedicated settlement services, English language programs (like the Adult Migrant English Program - AMEP), and workers' rights education is crucial for successful integration. Organizations like Multicultural Australia play a vital role in providing this support.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-amber-50 p-4 rounded-lg shadow">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-sky-600 mb-3">Employer Challenges in Sponsoring & Retaining</h3>
                        <p class="mb-2">Sponsoring and retaining international talent also poses specific challenges for childcare providers:</p>
                         <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 text-neutral-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Administrative Burden:</strong> The visa application and nomination processes are complex, requiring meticulous documentation, adherence to strict timelines, and ongoing compliance with Department of Home Affairs regulations. This can be time-consuming and daunting for smaller rural businesses.</li>
                            <li><strong>Financial Costs:</strong> Beyond the SAF levy and visa application fees, employers must ensure competitive wages that meet the CSIT and AMSR. Relocation assistance, if provided, adds to the financial outlay.</li>
                            <li><strong>Retention Issues:</strong> Despite sponsorship, retaining staff in rural areas can be difficult due to factors like isolation, limited social opportunities, perceived lower pay compared to metropolitan areas, and a lack of clear career progression pathways within smaller rural services. High turnover can negate the benefits of sponsorship.</li>
                            <li><strong>Integration Support:</strong> Employers are increasingly expected to provide or facilitate support for the integration of sponsored workers into the workplace and community, which can be an additional resource strain.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="mt-8 bg-stone-50 p-6 rounded-lg shadow">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-sky-600 mb-4 text-center">Government Initiatives & Support Programs</h3>
                    <p class="mb-4 text-center text-neutral-700">Both federal and state governments have recognized the critical nature of the childcare workforce shortage and have implemented various programs and initiatives to support the ECEC sector, providers, and rural communities. These programs aim to alleviate financial pressures, enhance skills, and improve living conditions, making rural placements more attractive and sustainable.</p>
                    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
                        <div class="p-3 bg-white rounded shadow">
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-800">Workforce Retention & Incentives</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Programs like the "Worker Retention Payment" offer financial incentives to ECEC providers who commit to increasing staff wages and limiting fee growth. Additionally, some initiatives provide discounted childcare for ECEC employees, aiming to attract and retain staff within the sector.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="p-3 bg-white rounded shadow">
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-800">Grants & Funding for Providers</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Providers can access funding through programs like the Community Child Care Fund (CCCF), which supports services in disadvantaged or vulnerable communities. Minor capital works grants are also available for sessional kindergartens in low socio-economic and rural and remote areas.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="p-3 bg-white rounded shadow">
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-800">Workforce Development & Training</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Initiatives such as the Practicum Placement Grant support students undertaking practical placements, while the Qualifications Pathways Program (QPP) assists existing workers in upskilling. The Rural & Remote Residential Program and the Remote Area Teacher Education Program (RATEP) are specific programs designed to develop and support ECEC professionals in regional and remote areas.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="p-3 bg-white rounded shadow">
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-800">Housing Assistance (Potential Models)</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">While direct housing assistance for sponsored childcare workers is not explicitly detailed, the Rural and Remote Hardship Incentive Scheme (RRHIS) for teachers in Queensland state schools provides a potential model. This scheme offers relocation assistance and reasonable housing costs for up to 12 months, including temporary accommodation and a taxable rental allowance, often placing teachers in department-provided housing at no cost. The Queensland government's broader "Homes for Queenslanders" plan aims to deliver one million new homes over 20 years, including social and affordable housing across regional Queensland, which could indirectly ease housing pressures for essential workers. Additionally, organizations like HOPE Housing offer co-investment models for essential workers (including childcare workers) to purchase homes, currently in Greater Sydney but indicating a potential private sector solution.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                     <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
                        These government and sector-led initiatives are vital components of a holistic strategy to address the rural childcare crisis. Exploring these options is crucial for both employers seeking to attract and retain talent, and for candidates considering a move to regional Queensland, as they can significantly enhance the viability and attractiveness of rural placements.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

         <section id="app-vision" class="pt-16 -mt-16 mb-12">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-sky-700 mb-8 text-center">The Vision: A Dedicated Recruitment App</h2>
            <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
                <p class="mb-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
                    The strategic report this navigator is based on culminates in recommending the development of a dedicated application. This app would aim to streamline the complex, multi-faceted process of connecting rural Queensland childcare providers with international candidates seeking sponsorship, thereby directly addressing the critical workforce shortages. This section outlines the core functionality, enhanced features, the significant market gap it would fill, and its potential for sustainable revenue success.
                </p>
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div class="bg-amber-50 p-4 rounded-lg shadow">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-sky-600 mb-3">Core App Functionality Envisioned:</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Employer Portal:</strong> A comprehensive dashboard offering step-by-step guidance for Standard Business Sponsorship (SBS) application, tools for nomination support (including templates and checklists), financial calculators for SAF levy and CSIT, and compliance checklists to ensure adherence to immigration regulations.</li>
                            <li><strong>Candidate Portal:</strong> An intuitive interface for visa eligibility self-assessment (covering SID 482, DAMA, and Training 407 visas), detailed guidance on ACECQA assessments (with links and checklists), a work experience calculator, an English proficiency checker, and secure document management for visa applications.</li>
                            <li><strong>Matching Algorithm:</strong> A sophisticated system that intelligently connects employers and candidates based on a wide range of criteria, including qualifications, relevant work experience, specific visa eligibility (standard SID vs. DAMA pathways), regional preferences, and the employer's sponsorship capabilities (e.g., approved SBS status, DAMA participation, ability to meet CSIT through various guaranteed earnings).</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                     <div class="bg-amber-50 p-4 rounded-lg shadow">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-sky-600 mb-3">Enhanced Features for Rural Context:</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-700 space-y-1">
                            <li><strong>Relocation & Integration Hub:</strong> A dedicated section providing vital resources for housing (e.g., local real estate listings, temporary accommodation options), information on community integration programs, and directories of local support networks and settlement services.</li>
                            <li><strong>Retention Support:</strong> Resources focused on long-term retention, including information on professional development opportunities, clear career pathways within the Australian ECEC sector, and details on government incentives designed to encourage staff to stay in rural areas.</li>
                            <li><strong>Cultural Competency Resources:</strong> Training modules and resources for employers to foster a culturally inclusive workplace, alongside integration resources for candidates to help them adapt to Australian culture and community life.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="mt-8 p-6 bg-stone-100 rounded-lg shadow">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-sky-600 mb-4 text-center">Filling a Critical Market Gap</h3>
                    <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">
                        The proposed app addresses a significant market gap in the Australian childcare sector, particularly in rural and regional areas. Currently, the process of sponsoring international workers is fragmented, complex, and lacks a centralized, user-friendly platform. Employers struggle with navigating intricate immigration laws, demonstrating genuine need, and managing compliance, often relying on expensive migration agents or internal resources that may lack specialized expertise. International candidates, on the other hand, face challenges in identifying legitimate sponsorship opportunities, understanding complex visa requirements, and accessing reliable information about rural living and integration support.
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">
                        This results in prolonged recruitment cycles, increased administrative burden, and a high turnover rate for sponsored workers due to inadequate support. The app would fill this void by providing a one-stop solution that simplifies the entire journey, from initial eligibility assessment and job matching to visa application support and post-arrival integration resources. By centralizing information and automating key processes, it would reduce friction, lower costs, and significantly improve efficiency for all stakeholders, directly contributing to alleviating the rural childcare crisis.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="mt-8 p-6 bg-stone-100 rounded-lg shadow">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-sky-600 mb-4 text-center">Pathways to Revenue Success</h3>
                    <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">
                        The dedicated recruitment app holds strong potential for sustainable revenue generation through a multi-faceted business model, leveraging its value proposition to both employers and candidates:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 text-neutral-700 space-y-2">
                        <li>
                            <strong>Employer Subscription Tiers (SaaS Model):</strong>
                            <p class="text-sm">Employers could subscribe to different tiers, offering varying levels of access to features. A basic tier might include job posting and candidate matching, while premium tiers could offer advanced compliance tools, dedicated support, integrated financial calculators, and access to a larger pool of pre-vetted candidates. This provides recurring revenue and scales with employer needs.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Candidate Premium Features (Freemium Model):</strong>
                            <p class="text-sm">While basic candidate features (e.g., profile creation, job browsing) would be free to attract a large user base, premium features could be offered for a fee. This might include advanced visa eligibility reports, personalized ACECQA assessment preparation, access to exclusive rural job listings, or expedited document review services. This caters to candidates seeking more comprehensive support.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Partnerships & Referrals:</strong>
                            <p class="text-sm">The app could generate revenue through partnerships with registered migration agents, English language testing providers, relocation services, and housing providers. Referral fees for successful placements or service subscriptions facilitated through the platform would create a robust ecosystem of support and revenue. Government grants or subsidies for addressing critical workforce shortages could also be explored.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Advertising & Data Insights:</strong>
                            <p class="text-sm">Targeted advertising for related services (e.g., professional development courses, insurance) could provide an additional revenue stream. Furthermore, anonymized and aggregated data insights on workforce trends, demand patterns, and successful migration pathways could be valuable to government bodies, industry associations, and educational institutions, offered as a premium data service.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="mt-4 text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">
                        By strategically combining these revenue streams, the app can establish a strong financial foundation while delivering immense value to the Australian childcare sector and supporting the growth of rural communities.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <p class="mt-6 text-md leading-relaxed">
                    By simplifying complex immigration processes, providing granular, up-to-date information, and fostering crucial connections with relocation and integration support services, such an application could significantly transform rural childcare recruitment. This, in turn, would contribute to greater workforce stability, foster sustainable growth in regional ECEC services, and ultimately enhance the liveability and economic prosperity of rural Queensland communities. This navigator serves as an an informational precursor, highlighting the key areas such a comprehensive app would address and the value it would bring.
                </p>

                <div class="mt-8 bg-stone-50 p-6 rounded-lg shadow">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-sky-600 mb-4 text-center">✨ Interactive App Matching Demo</h3>
                    <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-700">Experience a simplified simulation of how the app's matching algorithm could work. Enter your preferences to see a potential match.</p>
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <div>
                            <label for="demoDesiredRole" class="block text-sm font-medium text-neutral-700 mb-1">Desired Role:</label>
                            <select id="demoDesiredRole" class="w-full p-2 border border-stone-300 rounded-md focus:ring-sky-500 focus:border-sky-500">
                                <option value="">Select Role</option>
                                <option value="Childcare Worker">Childcare Worker</option>
                                <option value="Early Childhood Teacher">Early Childhood Teacher</option>
                                <option value="Family Day Care Worker">Family Day Care Worker</option>
                            </select>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <label for="demoYearsExperience" class="block text-sm font-medium text-neutral-700 mb-1">Years of Experience:</label>
                            <input type="number" id="demoYearsExperience" min="0" max="20" value="1" class="w-full p-2 border border-stone-300 rounded-md focus:ring-sky-500 focus:border-sky-500">
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <label for="demoPreferredRegion" class="block text-sm font-medium text-neutral-700 mb-1">Preferred Region (e.g., Townsville, Western Downs, Any Rural QLD):</label>
                            <input type="text" id="demoPreferredRegion" class="w-full p-2 border border-stone-300 rounded-md focus:ring-sky-500 focus:border-sky-500" value="Any Rural QLD">
                        </div>
                        <button id="runMatchingDemoBtn" class="w-full bg-sky-600 text-white py-2 px-4 rounded-md hover:bg-sky-700 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-sky-500 focus:ring-offset-2 transition duration-300">
                            Find My Match
                        </button>
                        <div id="matchingLoading" class="text-center text-sky-600 mt-2 hidden">Searching for matches...</div>
                        <div id="matchingOutput" class="mt-4 p-4 bg-white border border-stone-300 rounded-md llm-output hidden"></div>
                        <p class="text-xs text-neutral-500 mt-2">Disclaimer: This is a simulated demo for illustrative purposes only. Actual app matching would be more complex and real-time.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="bg-neutral-800 text-amber-50 py-8 text-center">
        <p class="text-sm">&copy; <span id="currentYear"></span> Rural Childcare Sponsorship Navigator. Information based on the "Sourcing Sponsored Childcare Professionals for Rural Queensland: A Strategic App Development Guide".</p>
        <p class="text-xs mt-1">This is an informational tool. Always consult official government sources and registered migration agents for definitive advice.</p>
